---
import Presentation from "../../../components/Presentation.astro";
import Divider from "../../../components/ui/Divider.astro";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";
import { Code as CodeSnippet } from "astro:components";

//#region CodeSnippets
const Figure1 = `
health = 100
print(health)

health = 50
print(health)`;
const Figure2 = `
100
50`;
const Figure3 = `
health = 100
print(health)

health = health - 20
print(health)`;
const Figure4 = `
100
80`;
const Task1 = `
health = 100
score = 0

print("Health:", health)
print("Score:", score)`;
const Task2 = `
health = 100
score = 0

print("Health:", health)
print("Score:", score)

health = health - 30
print("Health:", health)`;
const Task3 = `
health = 100
score = 0

print("Health:", health)
print("Score:", score)

health = health - 30
print("Health:", health)

score = score + 50
print("Score:", score)

score = score + 25
print("Score:", score)`;
const ExampleOutput = `
Health: 100
Score: 0
Health: 70
Score: 50
Score: 75`;
//#endregion
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/foce/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.5: Variable Reassignment</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.5</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">Variable Reassignment</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Changing Values Over Time</p>
              <p>Reassignment and Self-Referential Updates</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Reassigning a Variable</h2>
              <p>
                Once a variable exists, you can give it a new value at any
                time &mdash; just write the variable name and a new value.
                No <CodeSnippet
                  code="let"
                  lang={"python"}
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                  inline
                /> or special keyword needed in Python.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Reassigning a Variable</h2>
              <Code
                code={Figure1}
                frame="code"
                title="demo.py"
                lang="python"
                showLineNumbers={false}
                class="mb-3"
              />
              <Code
                code={Figure2}
                frame="terminal"
                lang="txt"
                title="Demo"
                showLineNumbers={false}
                class="fragment"
              />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Self-Referential Updates</h2>
              <p>
                A variable can even appear on <b>both sides</b> of the <CodeSnippet
                  code="="
                  lang={"python"}
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                  inline
                /> sign. Python evaluates the right side first using the
                <b>old</b> value, then stores the result as the <b>new</b> value.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Self-Referential Updates</h2>
              <Code
                code={Figure3}
                frame="code"
                title="demo.py"
                lang="python"
                showLineNumbers={false}
                class="mb-3"
              />
              <Code
                code={Figure4}
                frame="terminal"
                lang="txt"
                title="Demo"
                showLineNumbers={false}
                class="fragment"
              />
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Reassigning a variable's value</li>
                <li>Updating a variable based on its own current value</li>
                <li>Tracking a value as it changes over time</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Reassignment</dt>
                  <dd>Giving an existing variable a new value.</dd>
                  <dt>Self-Referential Update</dt>
                  <dd>
                    An assignment where a variable's current value is used to
                    compute its new value, like <CodeSnippet
                      code="health = health - 20"
                      lang={"python"}
                      theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                      inline
                    />.
                  </dd>
                  <dt>State</dt>
                  <dd>The current value(s) a program is keeping track of at a given moment.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new <b>Python</b> program named <b class="text-sn-theme"
              >1-5-reassignment.py</b
            >.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Start With a Value</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Create a <CodeSnippet
                code="health"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> variable set to <CodeSnippet
                code="100"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> and a <CodeSnippet
                code="score"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> variable set to <CodeSnippet
                code="0"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />.
            </li>
            <li>Print each variable with a label.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code
            code={Task1}
            frame="code"
            lang="python"
            title="1-5-reassignment.py"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "6" }}
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Take Damage</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Reassign <CodeSnippet
                code="health"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> to itself minus <CodeSnippet
                code="30"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />.
            </li>
            <li>Print the updated value with a label.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code
            code={Task2}
            frame="code"
            lang="python"
            title="1-5-reassignment.py"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "9" }}
            ins={{ range: "7-9" }}
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Earn Points</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Reassign <CodeSnippet
                code="score"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> to itself plus <CodeSnippet
                code="50"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />, then print it.
            </li>
            <li>
              Reassign <CodeSnippet
                code="score"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> to itself plus <CodeSnippet
                code="25"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> a second time, then print it again.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <Code
            code={Task3}
            frame="code"
            lang="python"
            title="1-5-reassignment.py"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "15" }}
            ins={{ range: "10-15" }}
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Challenge (Optional): Heal Up</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Reassign <CodeSnippet
                code="health"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> one more time to represent healing (add some points back),
              then print the updated value.
            </li>
            <li>Compare the final value to the value you started with.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={ExampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>
              What is the difference between declaring a variable and
              reassigning it?
            </li>
            <li>
              In <CodeSnippet
                code="health = health - 30"
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />, which value does Python use to compute the right side of the
              <CodeSnippet
                code="="
                lang={"python"}
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              /> &mdash; the old value or the new value?
            </li>
            <li>
              Why might a program need to update the same variable more than
              once while it's running?
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
